This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with video captioning, which is a task related to visual understanding. It also involves natural language processing (NLP) as it aims to generate captions for videos, which suggests that it could also belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category. The use of a mixture of experts model and external text corpus for topic embeddings suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the use of videos as input data suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
